Many `sjg` related errors are due to the incorrectly mapping the action used to return a JSON result available to the Struts2 jQuery Grid exposed by the plugin. So, to fix the error you should correctly map the url to the action.  For example

    &lt;s:url var=&quot;remoteurl&quot; namespace=&quot;/admin&quot; action=&quot;patients_getJsonData&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;sjg:grid
        id=&quot;gridtable&quot;
        caption=&quot;View Patients&quot;
        dataType=&quot;json&quot;
        href=&quot;%{#remoteurl}&quot;
        pager=&quot;true&quot;
        gridModel=&quot;patientList&quot;
        rowList=&quot;10,15,20&quot;
        rowNum=&quot;15&quot;
        rownumbers=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
        &lt;sjg:gridColumn name=&quot;email&quot; index=&quot;email&quot; title=&quot;Email&quot; sortable=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/sjg:grid&gt;

get the variable from the context, don&#39;t traverse the value stack.

To get JSON result from the URL referenced in the grid you don&#39;t need to use wildcards. Create the separate action configuration to get json data. For this action only params interceptor makes sense, other interceptors are vague. The action class should contain all necessary fields with getters/setters and properly initialized. See examples of the grid from the struts2 [jQuery Grid Showcase][1].

  [1]: https://struts.jgeppert.com/struts2-jquery-grid-showcase

